This has been replaced by simply running blackhole with -setup as an arg

Goals:

X 1. Make users maildir for user.
X 2. Make users mailbox dir in sendmail if non existant.
  3. Setup .qmail, .courier or .forward file for user.
  4. Undo .qmail, .courier or .forward file changes for user.
  5. Change .blackhole settings or /etc/blackhole.conf settings. 
  6. Write out changes back to the config file.
  7. Ability to work with the mysql DB and directly alter it.

